info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued September 26 at 6:16PM EDT by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT CENTRAL FLAGLER...SOUTHEASTERN ST. JOHNS AND SOUTHEASTERN PUTNAM COUNTIES THROUGH 700 PM EDT... At 615 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms capable of producing a landspout along a line extending from near Crescent Beach to Crescent City. Movement was northeast at 15 mph. HAZARD...Landspouts and wind gusts around 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Palm Coast, Bunnell, Crescent City, Andalusia, Marineland, Crescent Beach, Butler Beach, Beverly Beach, Espanola, and Dupont Center. LANDSPOUT...POSSIBLE MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.
